{
  "text": "The bio-physiological effects tend to be similar for a given species grown in the same environment [CITATION_1] . Stable oxygen isotopic ratios record source water, which contains a temperature signal, and leaf transpiration, controlled dominantly by vapor pressure deficit. There are some direct temperature effects on evaporative enrichment including a small effect on the difference in vapor pressure of the water containing heavy and lighter isotopes; however, the dominant control on degree of leaf enrichment for \u03b4",
